    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix dedicated NAS message list processing in RRC reconfiguration\n\n### Summary\nThere's an inconsistency in how dedicated NAS messages are processed in RRC reconfiguration versus DL information transfer. The RRC reconfiguration processing was using incorrect message types and memory management approaches.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Fixed the dedicated NAS message list processing in `nr_rrc_ue_process_rrcReconfiguration` to use consistent message types and memory management with DL information transfer processing\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen an RRC reconfiguration message contains a `dedicatedNAS_MessageList`, the UE may experience:\n- Incorrect NAS message handling due to wrong message type (`NAS_CONN_ESTABLI_CNF` instead of `NAS_DOWNLINK_DATA_IND`)\n- Potential memory issues from improper buffer management\n- NAS layer not receiving properly formatted messages\n\nThe issue manifests when the network sends RRC reconfiguration messages with dedicated NAS payloads during connection establishment or reconfiguration procedures.\n"
}